In the premium motorcycle helmets market, segmentation can be done based on the type of helmets available, the materials used in manufacturing, and the sales channels through which they are distributed. Premium motorcycle helmets come in various types such as full-face, half helmets, modular helmets, and open-face helmets. These cater to different preferences and purposes of motorcyclists. The materials used in premium helmets typically include carbon fiber, fiberglass, polycarbonate, or a combination of these materials to provide optimal protection and comfort to riders. In terms of sales channels, premium motorcycle helmets can be distributed through online retail, specialty stores, authorized dealers, and direct-to-consumer sales, catering to a diverse range of consumer preferences and convenience.

